We observe that the baselines achieve their best performance on KG-answerable queries. While QAnswer has a high coverage, the RP metric is quite low, even for KG-answerable queries. GoogleSDA has by design 100% precision in KG-answerable queries. While its coverage goes down drastically with increasing difficulty levels of the queries, barely above 5%, the RP remains respectable. {\mysystem} maintains a decent balance between coverage and RP values in all three scenarios.